edu.ncsu.csc216.travel.list_utils

Interface SimpleList<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - type of list element
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleArrayList

    public interface SimpleList<E>
    A simple generic list (ordered collection) interface adapted from java.util.List. List elements have zero-based indexes. List implementations can put restrictions on elements (such as no duplicate elements or null elements).
    Author:
    Jo Perry

      • add

        void add(int pos,
         E e)
        Inserts the specified element at the specified position in this list. Shifts any element currently at that position plus all subsequent elements to the right (adds one to their indexes).
        Parameters:
        pos - index at which the specified element is to be inserted
        e - element to be inserted
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified element is null and this list does not permit null elements
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if some property of the specified element prevents it from being added to this list
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is out of range
